%N A394089 Decimal expansion of  Sum_{k>=2} (-1)^k * (1 - 1/zeta(k)).
%C A394089 The asymptotic density of the numbers whose maximum exponent in their prime factorization is even (A368714).
%H A394089 Michael I. Shamos, <a href="https://euro.ecom.cmu.edu/people/faculty/mshamos/cat.pdf">Shamos's catalog of the real numbers</a>, 2007. See p. 312.
%F A394089 Equals 1 -  Limit_{m->oo} (1/m) * Sum_{k=1..m} A381955(k).
%F A394089 Equals -Sum_{k>=2} mu(k)/(k*(k+1)), where mu is the Moebius function (A008683) (Shamos, 2007).
%e A394089 0.275916720598227007690074960108226903989251367378136...
